[{"difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00105","question":"For national flights, which documents are provided?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc99","isCorrect":false,"choice":"National SIGWX charts only"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc9a","isCorrect":false,"choice":"WAFC upper wind and temp. charts only"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc9b","isCorrect":true,"choice":"both WAFC upper wind and temp. charts and National SIGWX charts"}],"explanation":"<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-15528\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/708A56C8-EE7C-4EB3-9B39-631BC2BB29F0.jpeg?resize=300%2C67&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"67\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/708A56C8-EE7C-4EB3-9B39-631BC2BB29F0.jpeg?resize=300%2C67&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/708A56C8-EE7C-4EB3-9B39-631BC2BB29F0.jpeg?resize=768%2C172&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/708A56C8-EE7C-4EB3-9B39-631BC2BB29F0.jpeg?resize=900%2C203&amp;ssl=1 900w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/708A56C8-EE7C-4EB3-9B39-631BC2BB29F0.jpeg?w=904&amp;ssl=1 904w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing","image":"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/708A56C8-EE7C-4EB3-9B39-631BC2BB29F0.jpeg?resize=300%2C67&ssl=1"},{"image":"","difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f000fd","question":"Who prepares national SIGWX charts?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc9c","isCorrect":false,"choice":"AMOs"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc9d","isCorrect":false,"choice":"WAFC"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc9e","isCorrect":true,"choice":"MWOS"}],"explanation":"<p>National Significant Weather Charts<br>\\nAll the four MWOs prepare SIGWX charts for their respective FIR and transmit to MWO Chennai, where these are compiled for making a single SIGWX chart. One single SIGWX chart is made for the medium level (between FL 100 and FL 250) and one for high level (between FL 250 and FL630). Zero degree isotherm is included for medium level chart. SIGWX charts are made four times a day based on 00, 06, 12 and 18 UTC data and issued 09 hr after the observation time and are valid for 24 hr.</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing"},{"image":"","difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00100","question":"When is briefing and consultation generally provided to aircrew relative to scheduled departure?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acc9f","isCorrect":true,"choice":"3 hr"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca0","isCorrect":false,"choice":"5 hr"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca1","isCorrect":false,"choice":"6 hr"}],"explanation":"<p>Briefing, Consultation and Display<br>\\nThe purpose of briefing is to provide the actual and forecast weather at the departing base, en-route, destination and alternate aerodromes. It is provided to the flight crew or operationspersonnel, in person, 3 hr priorto the scheduled departure. If not practical, it may be obtained through telephone or other telecommunication facilities.</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing"},{"difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00106","question":"For national flights, at which altitudes are winds and temperatures provided for low-level flights?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca2","isCorrect":true,"choice":"600, 1500 and 300 m"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca3","isCorrect":false,"choice":"3000 ft, 5000 ft, 10,000 ft"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca4","isCorrect":false,"choice":"600, 1000 and 500 m"}],"explanation":"<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-15529\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2116A84A-0E9F-403F-9EC4-1BCF82CE2751.jpeg?resize=300%2C67&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"67\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2116A84A-0E9F-403F-9EC4-1BCF82CE2751.jpeg?resize=300%2C67&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2116A84A-0E9F-403F-9EC4-1BCF82CE2751.jpeg?resize=768%2C172&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2116A84A-0E9F-403F-9EC4-1BCF82CE2751.jpeg?resize=900%2C203&amp;ssl=1 900w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2116A84A-0E9F-403F-9EC4-1BCF82CE2751.jpeg?w=904&amp;ssl=1 904w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing","image":"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2116A84A-0E9F-403F-9EC4-1BCF82CE2751.jpeg?resize=300%2C67&ssl=1"},{"image":"","difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00102","question":"For low-level and VFR flights, how long in advance is briefing provided?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca5","isCorrect":true,"choice":"FL150 or above in mountains"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca6","isCorrect":false,"choice":"FL110 above the sea"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca7","isCorrect":false,"choice":"FL 120 or over the plains"}],"explanation":"<p>Briefing for Low Level flights, and those under Visual Flight Rules, is given up to FL 100 (or up to FL 150 or above in mountains), poor visibility (5000m or less), any phenomena likely to lower widespread visibility to less than 5000 m, clouds which may affect flight, and SIGMET information.</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing"},{"difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00104","question":"How are height indications shown in flight documentation for all aerodrome meteorological conditions?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca8","isCorrect":true,"choice":"Above aerodrome elevation"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6acca9","isCorrect":false,"choice":"Flight Levels"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accaa","isCorrect":false,"choice":"As requested by the Pilot"}],"explanation":"<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-15526\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=300%2C52&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"52\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=300%2C52&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=1024%2C178&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=768%2C134&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?w=1052&amp;ssl=1 1052w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing","image":"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=300%2C52&ssl=1"},{"difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f000ff","question":"What types of weather, including fog and precipitation, are considered significant when visibility drops below 5000 m?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accab","isCorrect":false,"choice":"All level flights"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accac","isCorrect":false,"choice":"High level flights"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accad","isCorrect":true,"choice":"Low level flights"}],"explanation":"<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-15522\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/BA308535-A1A7-4583-8B1F-3ECF73646CBF.jpeg?resize=300%2C59&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"59\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/BA308535-A1A7-4583-8B1F-3ECF73646CBF.jpeg?resize=300%2C59&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/BA308535-A1A7-4583-8B1F-3ECF73646CBF.jpeg?resize=1024%2C201&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/BA308535-A1A7-4583-8B1F-3ECF73646CBF.jpeg?resize=768%2C151&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/BA308535-A1A7-4583-8B1F-3ECF73646CBF.jpeg?w=1079&amp;ssl=1 1079w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing","image":"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/BA308535-A1A7-4583-8B1F-3ECF73646CBF.jpeg?resize=300%2C59&ssl=1"},{"image":"","difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00101","question":"To whom is SIGMET information provided?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accae","isCorrect":false,"choice":"Low level flights"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accaf","isCorrect":true,"choice":"All level flights"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb0","isCorrect":false,"choice":"High level flights"}],"explanation":"<p>National Significant Weather Charts<br>\\nAll the four MWOs prepare SIGWX charts for their respective FIR and transmit to MWO Chennai, where these are compiled for making a single SIGWX chart. One single SIGWX chart is made for the <b>medium</b> level (between FL 100 and FL 250) and one for <b>high</b> level (between FL 250 and FL630). Zero degree isotherm is included for <b>medium</b> level chart. SIGWX charts are made four times a day based on 00, 06, 12 and 18 UTC data and issued 09 hr after the observation time and are valid for 24 hr.</p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing"},{"image":"","difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f000fe","question":"In which SIGWX charts is flight level of the freezing level included?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb1","isCorrect":true,"choice":"Medium level charts"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb2","isCorrect":false,"choice":"High level charts"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb3","isCorrect":false,"choice":"Low level charts"}],"explanation":"<p>National Significant Weather Charts<br>\\nAll the four MWOs prepare SIGWX charts for their respective FIR and transmit to MWO Chennai, where these are compiled for making a single SIGWX chart. One single SIGWX chart is made for the medium level (between FL 100 and FL 250) and one for high level (between FL 250 and FL630). Zero degree isotherm is included f<b>or medium level chart.</b> SIGWX charts are made four times a day based on 00, 06, 12 and 18 UTC data and issued 09 hr after the observation time and are valid for 24 hr.</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing"},{"difficulty":"medium","_id":"682e9d56d715cc08c3f00103","question":"How are height indications shown in flight documentation for en-route conditions?","choices":[{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb4","isCorrect":false,"choice":"Above aerodrome elevation"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb5","isCorrect":true,"choice":"Flight Levels"},{"_id":"692fba7bbff3ef35cc6accb6","isCorrect":false,"choice":"As requested by the Pilot"}],"explanation":"<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-15526\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=300%2C52&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"52\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=300%2C52&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=1024%2C178&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=768%2C134&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?w=1052&amp;ssl=1 1052w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\\n","subject":"Meteorology","book":"Pilot Shala Practice Set","topic":"Met & Briefing","image":"https://i0.wp.com/eatpl.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/15DFF485-2983-47C9-991A-C159145A2AA8.jpeg?resize=300%2C52&ssl=1"}]